Was able to skid along Calauan. Super laspag. But I still want to ride farther. Nabudol ng HS batchmate ko. Dapat hanggang Bay lang kami since mag pickup lang kami ng binili kong salabat tea sa isa ko pang HS batchmate. 

First night ride as well. Had some beer before bumalik ng Calamba from Los Banos. Kakatakot pag walang ilaw or safety equipment. 

Super nalaspag! Grabe. Gusto ko magtrain para makapagbike pa nang malayo

This workout will set up your power zones. Pay close attention to "how you feel" today. Today's intervals, or hard efforts, should feel like a 7-8 out of 10. Your breathing rate should be noticeably hard and continue to get harder as you progress into each interval. Be careful though, the goal of today is not only to do one interval but to do all four intervals. Pace yourself so you finish all four efforts within a 10-20 watt average of each other. At the end of the workout you will be asked if you want to use the result of the test to update your profile. If you select yes your threshold will be updated.

column5: This workout will focus on a combination of big gear, slow cadence, and small gear, high cadence efforts. The goal is to get your body more efficient in both gears. Pay close attention to the cadence demands and hit them spot on while staying within your power zones.
